THE Equality Court has ruled that the Black First Land First (BLF) political slogan "Land or Death" is hate speech. BLF has been ordered t write an apology to all South Africans within a period of one month. The apology should be published on the website of the South African Human Rights Commission. Furthermore, the organisation has been ordered to remove their political slogan "Land or Death" from their regalia, social media accounts and website within a month. Clerk of the Equality Court directed to send a copy of the judgment to the Director of Public Prosecutions for possible institution of criminal proceedings against the BLF and its leaders. 